@node "What's my dialer?" "What's my dialer?"

    Dialer is a very little and easy phone diary.

I made it to have always the ability to call my friends, parents,
girlfriends and so on... from my chair in front of my Amiga. With Dialer you
can store as many phone numbers as you want (or better, there's a limit, but
it's over 400 and I don't think you know so many people!!), but it's not
all: you can even dial the numbers directly from your Amiga.

You have two different ways: by @{"modem" link "Modem" 0} and by standard @{"audio" link "Audio" 0}.

I hope you enjoy this program and it can be useful for you as much as it's
for me!



Dialer is FREEWARE: this means that you can use it as much as you want for
free, but you cannot change it in any part and you must distribute with this
documentation. By the way, if you like it, please let @{"me" link "The author ME!!" 0} know... and if you
even want to pay a little fee, you'll be welcome!! :-))
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"

 INSTALLATION:

Just copy the program where you want!!! To run it, you have to double click
on its icon: very easy, isn't it?


The file with the records is saved in S: and it's called Dialer.dat
  ** Do not change it manually by yourself. **
@endnode

@node "How does it work?" "How does it work?"

 HOW DOES IT WORK?

Dialer has got 4 buttons:

1) ADD Click on it if you want to add a new item to your list. A new window
will pop up, asking you the surname, the name and the phone number. The name
and the surname must begin with an upper case letter, but Dialer will make
it for you if you forget.

2) EDIT Click on it if you want to edit the selected item of the listview
below. A window like the one of "Add" will pop up.

3) DELETE Click on it if you want to delete the selected item of the
listview below. A deleted item cannot be recovered anymore. So, be careful
since no confirmations are asked.

4) DIAL Dial the phone number of the selected item of the listview by audio
or by modem. You ca do it even double clicking on an item of the listview.


Then you can see 2 other buttons to select in which way the phone number
must be dialed:
 - @{"Audio" link "Audio" 0}
 - @{"Modem" link "Modem" 0}


There's a cycle button to decide if the list of users must be sorted by name
or by surname.


Dialer has also got three menu items: 1) INFO It displays some infos about
@{"theĀauthorĀ(me!!)" link "The author ME!!" 0}.

2) ICONIFY It iconifies Dialer: its window is closed and a title bar is
opened; click on the close gadget to reopen the Dialer. In this way, you can
have Dialer always in memory and you can run it whenever you want.

3) QUIT I bet you know what it does... :-)))
@endnode

@node "Possible problems" "Possible problems"

 POSSIBLE PROBLEMS

I hope Dialer is totally bug-free, but I know that no program can be.


@{"MODEM" link "Modem" 0}: Dialer seems to have some problems with some modems.

@{"AUDIO" link "Audio" 0}: Some speackers change the original sounds and it could cause that
       Dialer doesn't work properly.


I hope that's all!
@endnode

